# Geoguessr 

## Europe
#### Netherlands
Brick buildings like this are common in Western Europe
![brick building w europe.png](data:image/png;base64,)

The yellow number plate is common in NL, along with bicycles
![yellow plate NL.png](data:image/png;base64,)

#### Romania

These are commonly referred to as holey-poleys, they have long holes in the pole. There is white paint at the bottom which suggests it is indeed Romania.
![holey poleys romania.png](data:image/png;base64,)

These painted trees can also be found in Romania.
![romania painted tree 2.png](data:image/png;base64,)

## Asia
#### Malaysia
- Left hand drive
- White backed car
- White bollards with red rectangles
- White road lines, black and white curbs, but sometimes yellow shoulders
- Blue backed signs
#### Thailand
This is somewhat how Thai looks like. Typically Thai has a lot of straight letters. Northern Thailand tends to be a little foresty and mountainous.
